<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 6: CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS, RINGS AND
        SLEEVES - CYLINDER SLEEVES - METHOD ONE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
        <title>
            <emph type="underscr">METHOD ONE</emph>
        </title>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">"TELESCOPING GAUGE METHOD" (Refer to Figures
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600620">6.20</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600621">6.21</hotlnk>).
            </emph>
        </para>
        <para>Using a telescoping gauge
            <emph type="bold">OEM1022</emph>, and an outside micrometer:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure sleeve I.D. at top of piston ring travel (just below carbon ridge area) (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600620">6.20</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and record reading.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure sleeve I.D. below ring travel area (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600621">6.21</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and record reading.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The difference between two readings is cylinder sleeve taper. If specifications are
                exceeded, replace sleeve.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600619" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5231" filename="../figeg5/EG5231.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.19 Measuring Piston Pin O.D.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600620" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5339" filename="../figeg5/EG5339.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.20 Measuring Cylinder Sleeve I.D.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600621" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5340" filename="../figeg5/EG5340.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.21 Measuring Cylinder Sleeve Measurement Gauge</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
